it is planned as the routine return of a ship from an overhaul 
period said taylor 
the guidedmissile frigate has been in ingalls shipbuilding yard 
in pascagoula miss for the past nine months to repair the 
missile damage that left 37 crew members dead in may 1987 
the job was completed on time and was 52 million less than the 
estimate navy officials said 
the government of iraq has promised to pay the costs of 
repairing the ship and to compensate the families of those killed 
during the attack it will be presented a bill for the repairs 
