<TEXT>
president virgilio barco offered 
thursday to initiate peace talks with leftist guerrillas who 
launched their second big attack in a week in northern colombia 
barco introduced his peace plan on national television he said 
the talks should conclude with the dissolution of guerrilla 
organizations 
guerrillas must stop their terrorist acts human rights 
violations kidnappings and extortions before talks begin barco 
said he said a peace agreement should be reached by the time of 
the next presidential and parliamentary elections in march 1990 
guerrillas firing automatic assault rifles throwing hand 
grenades and setting fire to houses killed 12 peasants tuesday 
night gov jose gabriel amin of the state of cordoba said thursday 
the guerrilla attacks appear to be an effort by the rebels to 
force the government to open peace talks and make concessions 
an estimated 30 guerrillas of the peoples liberation army set 
fire to a ranch killed 10 peasants and wounded 15 tuesday near the 
town of canalete amin said 
canalete is about 320 miles north of the capital of bogota 
the insurgents then attacked the nearby village of el tomate 
setting fire to 26 huts and killing two people the governor said 
in a broadcast interview with the colombian radio chain rcn 
in el tomate a village of 600 people the attackers left 
messages painted on walls declaring death to the toads and 
paramilitaries survivors said in interviews with rcn 
guerrillas call army informants toads 
peasants in colombia have long claimed that they are caught 
between the army and the guerrillas 
in dozens of interviews with the associated press peasants have 
told of being forced to sell food and other necessities to 
guerrillas 
often the army hears of this and through threats or torture 
soldiers force the peasants to tell of guerrilla movements the 
peasants say 
the guerrillas then return and kill the peasants accusing them 
of being army informants the peasants have said 
the peoples liberation army and another guerrilla group known 
as the colombian revolutionary armed forces attacked the town of 
saisa in the state of cordoba on aug 23 and killed 12 civilians 
10 soldiers and two policemen the defense ministry said earlier 
twentytwo soldiers and policemen were taken prisoner the 
ministry said 
