against the seven manufacturers of agent orange 
but scientists are still trying to settle a continuing 
controversy over exactly what health effects the dioxin in agent 
orange may have 
dioxin is known to be one of the most powerful causes of cancer 
in laboratory animals ever tested it has not been shown to cause 
cancer in humans but the environmental protection agency 
classifies it as a probable carcinogen 
