attitudes toward the dissident writer but it is due to the number 
of soviet citizens who think solzhenitsyn is one of the best 
qualified people to serve on the committee said organizer yuri 
samadunov 
the 1970 nobel laureates masterwork the gulag archipelago 
traces the history of political repression in the soviet union and 
dwells at length on the purges and widespread repression that 
marred the 29year reign of stalin 
solzhenitsyn who spent eight years in labor camps under stalin 
was expelled from the soviet union after the publication of the 
gulag trilogy in the west he now lives in cavendish vt 
under soviet leader mikhail s gorbachev stalin and his legacy 
have come in for increasingly severe criticism in july the ruling 
communist party politburo approved the building of a monument in 
moscow to stalin victims 
