are made 
guerrilla violence has claimed more than 75000 lives in 20 
years and the estimated numerical strength of rebel groups has 
grown from 2500 to 10000 in a decade 
over the past year the guerrillas have blown up oil pipelines 45 
times attacked 14 towns set off car bombs attacked military 
bases ambushed army patrols and destroyed bridges electricity 
