protest of alleged corruption and discrimination against minorities 
by robeson county law enforcement officials 
the siege ended after 10 hours when gov jim martin agreed to 
form a state task force to investigate their allegations 
hatcher failed to surrender at the us marshals office in 
raleigh when his bond was revoked wednesday and a federal arrest 
warrant was issued thursday said chief deputy dwight rich jacobs 
surrendered wednesday 
if anything happens to my son i will hold the federal 
government responsible hatchers mother thelma clark said at a 
news conference outside a hospital where she underwent back surgery 
this week 
