hatcher and jacobs spent five months in jail before a 
threejudge panel of the 4th us circuit court of appeals ruled in 
june they had not been given a bond hearing soon enough after their 
arrest 
hatcher and jacobs were denied bond twice by a us magistrate 
and once by a us district court judge they were ordered back 
into custody when the entire appeals court agreed to reconsider the 
case at the request of assistant us attorney john bruce who 
challenged the terms of their release 
a lawyer representing hatcher said friday he has asked to have 
the federal warrant revoked because it was issued without a hearing 
and prosecutors had not demonstrated that hatcher posed a danger to 
