the probation even though she learned that mrs forster 18 is 
pregnant with her fourth child she said mrs forsters pregnancy 
didnt mean that the courts orders had been ignored since no 
method of birth control is foolproof 
mrs forster pleaded guilty in april to two counts of attempted 
child abuse stemming from a may 1987 incident in which she left her 
two sons william 1 and scott 6 months alone in a mesa 
apartment for three days authorities said the apartment had no air 
conditioning and both babies were dehydrated and near death when 
found 
the judge said at forsters sentencing that the birth control 
stipulation was the only way to make sure mrs forster did not have 
other children to abuse 
ms budzyns ruling friday came on motions filed by defense 
attorney garrett simpson mrs forsters public defender and 
