japan posted a current account surplus of 648 
billion in july down 11 percent from 728 billion a year earlier 
but up slightly from 643 billion in june the finance ministry 
said friday 
the current account is the broadest measure of trade and 
includes goods services and investment income plus various 
monetary transfers and aid payments 
the surplus in the trade of goods alone widened from the 
yearearlier level for the first time in 13 months going up to 
876 billion from 858 billion it also was up from a 738 
billion surplus registered in june 
the ministry said it is too early to conclude that japans 
downtrend in the trade surplus has come to a halt the july rise in 
the merchandise trade surplus had been reported in early august 
using a slightly different measure that made it the first such 
increase in 15 months 
the trade surplus the main target of criticism from the united 
states european countries and other major trade partners of japan 
had been declining consistently due to the yens sharp appreciation 
since 1985 a higher yen would restrain exports by making japanese 
goods less competitive abroad 
exports in july rose 168 percent over a year earlier to 228 
billion while imports surged 282 percent to a record 140 
billion 
